## Environment Variables
- `/implement` Phase 0 auto-detects required env vars based on requirements.json
- NEVER commit `.env.local`
- Commit `.env.example` with keys only

## Rules
- Reflect prototype/ designs as closely as possible
- TypeScript strict mode
- All API routes must have try-catch + NextResponse error handling
- Environment variables in .env.local (never commit)
- Server components first, "use client" only when necessary

## Vercel Deployment Constraints
- API route body size: 4.5MB limit
- Serverless function timeout: 60s (Pro plan 300s)
- Edge Runtime cannot use Node.js-specific APIs (fs, child_process, etc.)
- Must configure external image domains in `next.config.ts`
